		<li class="comment " id="comment-125869">
			<p class="comment_meta">
				<span class="comment_num"><a href="#comment-125869" title="Permalink to this comment">129</a></span>
				<strong>luke </strong>
				<span class="comment_time">// Feb 29, 2008 at 12:46 pm</span>
			</p>
			<div class="entry">
				<p>To reduce shrinkage, you need bacon that has not had water injected into it following the curing process &#8211; which is done to increase weight, for profit. Either that, or the bacon is not cured properly, but is commonly brined for 12-15 hours, making what we call &#8216;pickled pork&#8217;.  This leaves it with a high water content, which causes it to shrink when cooked. Ideally you want properly dry-cured bacon. only this will not shrink when cooked.</p>
 
							</div>
		</li>
		
			
